<HL>
   Business Brief -- Kumagai Gumi (Hong Kong) Ltd.:
   Earnings for Fiscal Half
   Fell 41% to $6 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
07/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   J.KMG
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Kumagai Gumi (Hong Kong) Ltd. said its profit for the half
ended March 31 slumped 41% to 47 million Hong Kong dollars
(US$6 million) from HK$79 million a year earlier.
   Earnings per share of the local arm of the Japanese
construction giant dropped 41% to 15.9 Hong Kong cents from
27.1 cents. The company didn't provide a reason for the
decline in profit, but predicted an improvement in the second
half.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Revenue grew 3.1% to HK$1.48 billion from HK$1.43 billion.
   Kumagai's board proposed an interim dividend of 10 Hong
Kong cents a share, down 33% from 15 Hong Kong cents.
</TEXT>
